    <!-- Title -->

   <h3>Description</h3>
    <p>In our daily language, we often use gender-coded words unintentionally. Society has some inherent expectations for men and women that inadvertently seep into the language we use. Think “nosy” and “energetic”: words we almost never use to describe men.</p>

    <p>This kind of gender coding in language also often appears in job ads, and research shows that women are less likely to apply for jobs containing masculine-coded language.</p>
    <h3>Instructions</h3>

    <p>This tool can be used to analyse job advertisements for any gender-coded words so that adjustments can be made to reduce the discouraging effect.
    <ul>
    <li>Step 1: Copy job advertisement description</li>
            <li>Step 2: Paste into the text box</li>
            <li>Step 3: Review gender-coded words</li>
            <li>Step 4: Adjust as needed</li>
        </ul>
        
    

